    <article><span>Food</span><h3>Stay close to nature.</h3><p>Choose whole, fibre-rich plant foods and reduce the distance between what nature provides and what reaches the plate.</p></article>
    <article><span>Rhythm</span><h3>Give digestion time.</h3><p>Avoid constant eating, leave considered gaps between meals and allow the body to complete one digestive cycle before beginning another.</p></article>
    <article><span>Evening</span><h3>Eat early and lightly.</h3><p>An earlier dinner and a clear gap before sleep can support digestion, rest and a steadier daily rhythm.</p></article>
